HEADWORD: Stringpiece
<hw>String"piece`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Arch.)</fld>
<sd>(a)</sd> <def>A long piece of timber, forming a margin or edge of
any piece of construction; esp.:</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>One of the
longitudinal pieces, supporting the treads and rises of a flight or run
of stairs.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

